    "recap_headline": "Davidson College Athletics",
    "recap_text": "DAVIDSON \u2014 Fordham scored 15 runs in the ninth inning and rolled to a 26-3 series-clinching win at Wilson Field Sunday afternoon.\nWith the loss, the Wildcats dropped to 9-9 overall and 1-2 in the Atlantic 10.\nFordham (8-10, 2-1) led 2-0 early before\nTheo Loughlin\ntied the game with a two-run single in the fourth. Then the Rams scored six in the fifth and three in the seventh to break open the game. But they did most of their damage in the ninth off nine hits, including a Madden Ocko grand slam, and two Wildcat errors.\nWill Brooks\nprovided the other Wildcat offensive highlight, an RBI-double in the seventh.\nStarter\nEd Hall\nthrew 4.2 innings in the loss.\nUp Next\nThe Wildcats are idle in the midweek and will play at A-10 foe La Salle next weekend."
